==Events== * [[218]] &ndash; [[Battle of Antioch (218)|Battle of Antioch]]: With the support of the Syrian [[Roman legion|legions]], [[Elagabalus]] defeats the forces of emperor [[Macrinus]]. He flees, but is captured near [[Chalcedon]] and later executed in [[Cappadocia]]. * [[452]] &ndash; [[Italy]] invaded by [[Attila the Hun]] * [[632]] &ndash; [[Muhammad]], Islamic [[prophet]], dies in [[Medina]]. * [[793]] &ndash; Vikings raid the abbey at [[Lindisfarne]] in Northumbria, commonly accepted as the beginning of [[Norse activity in the British Isles]]. *[[1042]] &ndash; [[Edward the Confessor]] becomes King of England, one of the last Anglo-Saxon kings of England. *[[1191]] &ndash; [[Richard I]] arrives in [[Acre, Israel|Acre]], beginning his crusade. *[[1405]] &ndash; [[Richard le Scrope]], the [[Archbishop of York]], and [[Thomas de Mowbray, 4th Earl of Norfolk|Thomas Mowbray]], [[Earl of Norfolk]], are executed in [[York]] on [[Henry IV of England|Henry IV]]'s orders. *[[1776]] &ndash; [[American Revolutionary War]]: American attackers are driven back at the [[Battle of Trois-Rivières]]. *[[1783]] &ndash; [[Laki]], a [[volcano]] in [[Iceland]], begins an eight-month eruption which kills over 9,000 people and starts a seven-year [[famine]]. *[[1789]] &ndash; [[James Madison]] introduces [[United States Bill of Rights|twelve proposed amendments to the United States Constitution]] in Congress. *[[1794]] &ndash; [[Maximilien Robespierre|Robespierre]] inaugurates the [[French Revolution]]'s new state religion, the [[Cult of the Supreme Being]], with large organized festivals all across France. *[[1856]] &ndash; A group of 194 [[Pitcairn Islands|Pitcairn Islanders]], descendants of the mutineers of {{HMS|Bounty}}, arrives at [[Norfolk Island]], commencing the Third Settlement of the Island. *[[1861]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Tennessee]] secedes from the [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]]. *[[1862]] &ndash; American Civil War: [[Battle of Cross Keys]]: [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] forces under General [[Stonewall Jackson]] save the [[Army of Northern Virginia]] from a Union assault on the James Peninsula led by General [[George B. McClellan]]. *[[1867]] &ndash; Coronation of [[Franz Joseph I of Austria|Franz Joseph]] as [[King of Hungary]] following the Austro-Hungarian compromise (''[[Ausgleich]]''). *[[1887]] &ndash; [[Herman Hollerith]] applies for US [[patent]] #395,781 for the 'Art of Compiling Statistics', which was his [[punched card]] [[calculator]]. *[[1906]] &ndash; [[Theodore Roosevelt]] signs the [[Antiquities Act]] into law, authorizing the President to restrict the use of certain parcels of [[public land]] with historical or conservation value. *[[1912]] &ndash; [[Carl Laemmle]] incorporates [[Universal Studios|Universal Pictures]]. *[[1918]] &ndash; Nova Aquila, brightest nova since Kepler's nova of 1604, discovered *[[1918]] &ndash; A [[Solar eclipse of June 8, 1918|solar eclipse]] is observed at [[Baker City, Oregon]] by scientists and an artist hired by the United States Navy. *[[1928]] &ndash; [[Second Northern Expedition]]: The [[National Revolutionary Army]] captures [[Peking]], whose name is changed to Beijing ("Northern Capital"). *[[1929]] &ndash; [[Margaret Bondfield]] is appointed [[Secretary of State for Employment|Minister of Labour]]. She is the first woman appointed to the [[Cabinet of the United Kingdom]]. *[[1940]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: The completion of [[Operation Alphabet]], the evacuation of Allied forces from [[Narvik]] at the end of the [[Norwegian Campaign]]. *[[1941]] &ndash; World War II: The [[Allies of World War II|Allies]] commence the [[Syria&ndash;Lebanon Campaign]] against the possessions of [[Vichy France]] in the [[Levant]]. *[[1942]] &ndash; World War II: The Japanese imperial submarines [[Japanese submarine I-21|I-21]] and I-24 shell the Australian cities of Sydney and [[Newcastle, New South Wales|Newcastle]]. *[[1949]] &ndash; [[Helen Keller]], [[Dorothy Parker]], [[Danny Kaye]], [[Fredric March]], [[John Garfield]], [[Paul Muni]] and [[Edward G. Robinson]] are named in an [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] report as [[Communist Party]] members. * 1949 &ndash; [[George Orwell]]'s ''[[Nineteen Eighty-Four]]'' is published. *[[1953]] &ndash; [[1953 Flint&ndash;Beecher tornado|An F5 tornado]] hits [[Beecher, Michigan]], killing 116, injuring 844, and destroying 340 homes. * 1953 &ndash; The [[Supreme Court of the United States|United States Supreme Court]] rules that restaurants in Washington, D.C. cannot refuse to serve black patrons. *[[1959]] &ndash; The {{USS|Barbero|SS-317|6}} and [[United States Postal Service]] attempt the delivery of mail via [[Missile Mail]]. *[[1966]] &ndash; An [[F-104 Starfighter]] collides with [[XB-70 Valkyrie]] prototype no. 2, destroying both aircraft during a photo shoot near [[Edwards Air Force Base]]. [[Joseph A. Walker]], a [[NASA]] test pilot, and Carl Cross, a [[United States Air Force]] test pilot, are both killed. * 1966 &ndash; [[Topeka, Kansas]], is devastated by a tornado that registers as an "F5" on the [[Fujita scale]]: The first to exceed US$100&nbsp;million in damages. Sixteen people are killed, hundreds more injured, and thousands of homes damaged or destroyed. * 1966 &ndash; The [[National Football League]] and [[American Football League]] announced a [[AFL–NFL merger|merger]] effective in [[1970 NFL season|1970]]. *[[1967]] &ndash; [[Six-Day War]]: The [[USS Liberty incident|USS ''Liberty'' incident]] occurs, killing 34 and wounding 171. *[[1972]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: Nine-year-old [[Phan Thị Kim Phúc]] is burned by [[napalm]], an event captured by [[Associated Press]] photographer [[Nick Ut]] moments later while the young girl is seen running down a road, in what would become an iconic, [[Pulitzer Prize]]-winning photo. *[[1982]] &ndash; [[Bluff Cove Air Attacks]] during the [[Falklands War]]: Fifty-six British servicemen are killed by an [[Argentine]] air attack on two landing ships, [[RFA Sir Galahad|RFA ''Sir Galahad'']] and {{ship|RFA|Sir Tristram|L3505|6}}. *[[1984]] &ndash; [[Homosexuality]] is declared legal in the [[States and territories of Australia|Australian state]] of [[New South Wales]]. *[[1987]] &ndash; New Zealand's [[New Zealand Labour Party|Labour]] government establishes a [[New Zealand nuclear-free zone|national nuclear-free zone]] under the [[New Zealand Nuclear Free Zone, Disarmament, and Arms Control Act 1987]]. *[[1992]] &ndash; The first [[World Oceans Day]] is celebrated, coinciding with the [[Earth Summit]] held in [[Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil. *[[1995]] &ndash; Downed U.S. Air Force pilot [[Captain (United States O-3)|Captain]] [[Scott O'Grady]] is rescued by [[U.S. Marines]] in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnia]]. *[[2001]] &ndash; [[Mamoru Takuma]] kills eight and injures 15 in [[Osaka school massacre|a mass stabbing]] at an elementary school in the [[Osaka Prefecture]] of [[Japan]]. *[[2004]] &ndash; The first [[Transit of Venus, 2004|Venus Transit]] in well over a century takes place, the previous one being in [[1882]]. *[[2007]] &ndash; [[Newcastle, New South Wales]], Australia, is hit by the State's worst storms and flooding in 30 years resulting in the death of nine people and the grounding of a trade ship, the {{MV|Pasha Bulker}}. *[[2008]] &ndash; At least 37 miners go missing after an explosion in an [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] coal mine causes [[2008 Ukraine coal mine collapse|it to collapse]]. * 2008 &ndash; At least seven people are killed and ten injured in [[Akihabara massacre|a stabbing spree]] in [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]. *[[2009]] &ndash; Two American [[journalist]]s are [[2009 imprisonment of American journalists by North Korea|found guilty]] of illegally entering [[North Korea]] and sentenced to 12 years of [[penal labour]]. *[[2014]] &ndash; At least 28 people are killed in an [[2014 Jinnah International Airport attack|attack at Jinnah International Airport, Karachi, Pakistan]].
